Nonetheless, it is still possible to identify a few features in the luminescence pulse that can be assigned to a specific decay channel. As can be derived from Fig. 4a, the first decay time constant exhibits a gradual increase with cooling but below 30 K it settles at τ1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
